Polyus, Tatneft, Mail.ru, Norilsk: Russian Equity Market Preview

-- B y   A n n a   S h i r y a e v s k a y a
-- 
2011-04-25T21:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-25/polyus-tatneft-mail-ru-norilsk-russian-equity-market-preview.html
The following companies may be
active in Russian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and
share prices are from the previous close of trading in Moscow.  The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  retreated 1.3 percent to 1,769.94.  OAO Polyus Gold (PLZL RX): The largest gold producer in
 Russia  reports 2010 financial results. Polyus Gold declined 1.4
percent to 1,752.50 rubles.  OAO  Tatneft (TATN)  (TATN3 RX): Tatneft reports 2010 financial
results. The oil producer based in Russia’s Tatarstan region
declined 2.2 percent to 184.46 rubles.  Mail.ru Group Ltd. (MAIL)  : The Russian investor in
Facebook Inc. plans to report financial results. Mail.ru rose
0.8 percent to $35.94 in  London .  OAO GMK Norilsk Nickel (GMKN RX): The world’s biggest
producer of nickel won’t make new proposals to buy back shares
from billionaire Oleg Deripaska’s United Co. Rusal, RIA Novosti
said today, citing the company’s President Andrey Klishas.
Norilsk Nickel fell 2 percent to 7,548 rubles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
